Title: Chief Scientist - AI 
Location: San Francisco Bay Area - Palo Alto, California 
Who We Are 
Cheetah Mobile (NYSE: CMCM) is a leading, profitable global mobile internet company founded and based in Beijing, China. We also have built our dual HQ in Palo Alto, California. We aim to provide the best apps for mobile users worldwide, while building a leading global mobile ad platform for advertisers. Our mission is to Make the World Smarter. 
Our mission critical applications, including Clean Master, CM Security, Battery Doctor and Duba Anti-virus, help make the internet and mobile experience speedier, simpler, and safer for users worldwide. We have 600+ million global mobile monthly active users, and weâ€™re continuing to grow! We also provide multiple user traffic entry points and global content promotional channels capable of delivering targeted content to hundreds of millions of users. 
We invest in the latest technologies and trends, such as robotics, artificial intelligence, and data-driven content strategies. 
Learn more about us at: www.cmcm.com 
What will you be doingâ€¦ 
Cheetah Mobile is looking for a Chief Scientist in AI to lead Cheetah Research Lab in Palo Alto. We are committed to advancing the field of artificial intelligence by building technologies to help our users create a deeper connection with the world around us. Weâ€™re looking for talented individuals interested in: deep learning, natural language processing (NLP), machine translation, video analysis, computer vision, computational statistics, speech, images, and applied mathematics. 
Responsible for the development strategy, technical path, and key technology direction 
Lead research in advanced Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning, majorly focusing on the long-term research topics 
Build up and lead a team of machine learning scientists evolving distinctive practices 
Publication, presentation, and contribution as a thought leader in the field of machine learning and AI 
What we are looking for: 
Ph.D. in Machine Learning or related fields from a highly reputable institution 
8+ years of hands-on research experience in Deep Learning and related fields, industrial experience required 
Highly cited publications in relevant fields 
Deep insight in machine learning and deep learning 
Extensive experience in natural language process (NLP), Machine translation, and/or video analysis 
Experience with Caffe/TensorFlow/Torch or similar deep learning frameworks 
Programming experience with R/Scala/C++/Python, or other related programming languages 
Strong passion in technology and willingness to make an impact 
